President Donald J. Trump met with President Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic of Croatia to discuss ways to strengthen relations between the two countries. They both expressed a commitment to supporting stability and security in the western Balkans. President Trump encouraged President Grabar-Kitarovic to promote regional reconciliation. President Trump also praised Croatia's efforts to promote energy security and diversification, and expressed support for the timely completion of the Krk Island liquefied natural gas facility.